(1515, 0, '2011-01-24 23:32:16', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Video-installation artist Mika Rottenberg creates mini-factories, farms, and tableaux, which produce products variously made by tremendously fat, tall, muscled, long-haired or long-fingernailed women. Women, who in their own lives commodify their eccentricities, are, in Rottenberg''s films, featured as "bearers of production." To make their merchandise, the protagonists have to pedal, squeeze, cry, sweat, massage, dig, push, burrow, morph, cross continents, and use more than a bit of alchemy. Every detail and orthodoxy is taken to its extremes, turned upside down. You smell the flowers and sweat; you hear the sounds of breathing, nails tapping, sweat sizzling, milk hitting tin; you feel the breezes, and the squeezing of flesh, its bursting out of constraints. Yet Rottenberg treats the superabundance with such normalcy it makes me laugh.', 'Mika Rottenberg - Squeeze - 2010', '', 'pending', 'open', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2011-01-24 23:32:16', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', 0, 'http://rawwar.org/?p=1515', 0, 'post', '', 0),
