(1244, 1, '2011-01-17 23:12:13', '2011-01-17 23:12:13', 'uses appropriated images of Wonder Woman to subvert the ideology and meaning embedded in the television series.[1] "Opening with a prolonged salvo of fiery explosions accompanied by the warning cry of a siren, Technology/Transformation: Wonder Woman is supercharged, action-packed, and visually riveting... throughout its nearly six minutes we see several scenes featuring the main character Diana Prince... in which she transforms into the famed superero."', 'Dara Birnbaum - Technology/transformation: Wonder Woman - 1978 - 1979', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1186-revision', '', '', '2011-01-17 23:12:13', '2011-01-17 23:12:13', '', 1186, 'http://184.106.93.224/?p=1244', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
